{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9c677eb1-9b26-40ab-ab56-53c28e1c5d2c","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n| VSTest flag | Microsoft.Testing.Platform flag |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nEverything after `--` is forwarded to the test platform runner. The `--filter` stays before `--` so `dotnet test` handles it.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cb0128fe-cae6-4b72-a327-857825ec023d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration, not a codebase task. Let me provide the answer directly.\n\nKey changes when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. `dotnet test` still works but the underlying runner changes\n2. `--filter` → `--filter` (still works, but the new native way is `--filter`)\n3. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (native option)\n4. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect code-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage package, or you can use `--coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura`\n\n\n5. `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`, `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`, and `--blame-hang-timeout` → `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nThere are two execution paths: running through `dotnet test` which acts as a host/orchestrator where many legacy switches still work with translation, or invoking the test executable directly. The `dotnet test` command interface has changed significantly with the new platform.\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the flag mappings are: `--filter` remains `--filter` but supports `--treenode-filter` for native syntax, `--logger trx` requires the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package and becomes `--report-trx`, code coverage needs `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` and uses `--collect code-coverage` or `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`, and blame becomes `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` with timeout options. The new-style flags are passed after a `--` separator when using `dotnet test` as the orchestrator. I need to clarify the filter syntax and NuGet dependencies for Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8, since the compatibility layer handles VSTest filters but there are specific packages required for each feature like TRX reporting, code coverage, and dump collection.\n\nBuilding the command...","outputTokens":1463,"requestId":"E83E:11815A:26B89D7:2933631:6A049406"},"id":"4b72e32c-0139-4202-8a41-7d4c55f3744d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:23.525Z","parentId":"97125939-cdca-48ff-9813-c703727b4fef"}
